# AI Governance Controls (Development-Time Enforcement)

These rules enforce the 10 mandatory AI governance controls defined in `docs/AI_GOVERNANCE_FRAMEWORK.md`. They apply to all code, configuration, and documentation changes across the MedinovAI platform.

## 1. Model Risk Register (GOV-01)

Before deploying any AI model, prompt, or pipeline change:
- Verify the model is registered in the Model Risk Register (`templates/ai-ml/config/model_risk_register_schema.json`).
- If creating a new AI model or integrating a new vendor model, a registry entry MUST be created before any deployment.
- Every model must have a `risk_class`, `impact_classification`, and `mitigation_plan` with a defined `fallback_mechanism`.
- No unregistered AI model may run in production.

## 2. Pre-Deployment Validation (GOV-02)

- All AI model changes must pass the pre-deployment validation pipeline (`workflows/ai-model-validation.lobster.md`) before reaching production.
- This includes: benchmark evaluation, bias audit, explainability check, shadow deployment, and approval gates.
- Clinical-use models require Chief Medical Officer approval.
- Never bypass the validation pipeline. There are no shortcuts for patient safety.

## 3. Bias Testing (GOV-03)

- Every AI model that affects patient care must be tested for bias across demographics before deployment.
- Use the formal Bias Testing Protocol (`templates/ai-ml/skills/bias-testing/SKILL.md`).
- Demographics to test: age, sex, race/ethnicity, language, socioeconomic status, disability status.
- If you are adding or modifying an AI model, ensure bias testing is included in your testing plan.
- A model that fails bias testing CANNOT be deployed until remediation is complete and approved.

## 4. Human Override Pathways (GOV-04)

- Every AI recommendation presented to a clinician MUST include an override mechanism.
- Overrides must not add friction or penalty to the clinician's workflow.
- When building clinician-facing AI features, always implement:
  - An explicit override action (equally accessible as accept)
  - Override audit logging (who, when, what, why)
  - No punitive metrics tied to override frequency
- Reference: `templates/ai-ml/AGENTS.md` and `templates/clinical/AGENTS.md` (Human Override Pathways sections).

## 5. Explainability Standards (GOV-05)

- All AI outputs must include explainability fields proportional to the model's risk class.
- Reference the Explainability Standards (`templates/ai-ml/config/explainability_standards.md`) for required fields per tier:
  - Low risk: `confidence_score`, `ai_generated`
  - Medium risk: + `contributing_factors`
  - High risk: + `reasoning_chain`, `data_sources`
  - Critical risk: + `uncertainty_quantification`, `alternative_recommendations`, `limitations`
- All AI-generated content MUST be labeled as AI-generated (`ai_generated: true`).
- When designing AI output schemas, include these fields from the start. Do not add them as an afterthought.

## 6. Performance Monitoring (GOV-06)

- Every deployed AI model must have heartbeat monitoring for accuracy drift, alert fatigue, and clinical outcomes.
- Reference: `templates/ai-ml/HEARTBEAT.md` (checks #9, #10, #11, #12).
- When deploying a model, ensure:
  - Baseline performance metrics are captured during shadow deployment.
  - Drift detection thresholds are configured (default: 5% alert, 10% auto-disable).
  - Alert-to-action ratios are tracked for clinician-facing alerts.

## 7. Data Lineage Tracking (GOV-07)

- Every data source feeding into an AI model must have a lineage record conforming to `templates/data/config/data_lineage_schema.json`.
- When creating or modifying data pipelines:
  - Document every transformation step with input/output hashes.
  - Record PHI handling at each step.
  - Link data sources to consuming models in the Model Risk Register.
  - Document consent basis and retention policy.
- Reference: `templates/data/AGENTS.md` (Data Lineage Tracking section).

## 8. Vendor Accountability (GOV-08)

- When integrating any third-party AI model, API, or service:
  - Ensure a vendor contract exists with terms from `templates/docs-standards/vendor-ai-accountability-terms.md`.
  - Record the contract reference in the Model Risk Register (`vendor_contract_ref` field).
  - Verify the vendor provides: model documentation, performance benchmarks, known limitations, and change notification.
- Never integrate a vendor AI model without a signed accountability agreement.

## 9. Incident Response (GOV-09)

- When encountering AI model failures, anomalous behavior, or suspected patient impact:
  - Follow the AI Incident Response Protocol (`templates/ai-ml/skills/ai-incident-response/SKILL.md`).
  - Classify severity: AI-Sev1 (patient harm), AI-Sev2 (potential harm/threshold breach), AI-Sev3 (degraded accuracy).
  - Quarantined models may NOT be re-enabled without full re-validation (GOV-02) and governance board approval (Sev1).
- When building AI features, always implement a model quarantine mechanism and fallback.

## 10. Cross-Functional Oversight (GOV-10)

- New clinical AI deployments require AI Governance Board approval.
- Critical-risk model deployments require governance board chair sign-off.
- Reference: `docs/AI_GOVERNANCE_BOARD.md` for board composition, authority, and escalation paths.
- Any team member may escalate AI concerns to the governance board at any time.

## Quick Reference

| When you are... | Check these controls |
|-----------------|---------------------|
| Creating a new AI model | GOV-01 (register), GOV-02 (validate), GOV-03 (bias test), GOV-05 (explainability) |
| Modifying a production model | GOV-02 (re-validate), GOV-03 (re-test bias), GOV-06 (update monitoring) |
| Building clinician-facing AI features | GOV-04 (override pathway), GOV-05 (explainability), GOV-06 (alert fatigue) |
| Integrating a vendor AI | GOV-01 (register), GOV-08 (vendor terms), GOV-02 (validate) |
| Creating a data pipeline for AI | GOV-07 (lineage tracking) |
| Responding to an AI incident | GOV-09 (incident response), GOV-10 (escalation) |
| Deploying to production | GOV-02 (full pipeline), GOV-10 (board approval if clinical) |
